The paper discusses the use of information criteria to characterize the generalization of deep learning models, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also explores the interplay between noise and curvature in deep models, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the Hessian matrix and covariance matrix, which are concepts from information theory (cs.IT).
